Explorative Data analysis¶

Exloring:¶

Target¶

  • Stroke ### Socio Demographical
  • Age
  • Gender
  • ever_married
  • work_type
  • Residence_type ### Clincal Conditions
  • hypertension
  • heart_disease
  • avg_glucose_level
  • bmi ### Behavioural
  • smoking_status

Metadata from Kaggle¶

Attribute Information 1) id: unique identifier 2) gender: "Male", "Female" or "Other" 3) age: age of the patient 4) hypertension: 0 if the patient doesn't have hypertension, 1 if the patient has hypertension 5) heart_disease: 0 if the patient doesn't have any heart diseases, 1 if the patient has a heart disease 6) ever_married: "No" or "Yes" 7) work_type: "children", "Govt_jov", "Never_worked", "Private" or "Self-employed" 8) Residence_type: "Rural" or "Urban" 9) avg_glucose_level: average glucose level in blood 10) bmi: body mass index 11) smoking_status: "formerly smoked", "never smoked", "smokes" or "Unknown"* 12) stroke: 1 if the patient had a stroke or 0 if not

Our Calculated fields¶

13) bmi_imp: imputed median 14) smoking_imp: imputed modus 15) rounded_age: rounded age if original value had decimals

Target Variable: Stroke¶

In [24]:
plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
counts= df["stroke"].value_counts()
plt.style.use("grayscale")

plt.pie(counts, labels=['NO','YES'], autopct='%1.1f%%', colors=['c', 'orange'])
plt.title('Distribution of Stroke')
plt.show()

plt.ylabel("Age")
plt.legend(title="Stroke", loc="upper right")
